 According to witnesses, rescue services got to the school after two hours.
 One of the administrators at the institution pointed out that the affected dormitory had been occupied by Form One students.
 Dr Matiang’i added that the school will be closed to allow students recover from shock.
 "The school will remain closed for the next two weeks to allow the students to recover from the shock of the incident," he stated.
 Matiang'i also sent condolences on behalf of President Uhuru Kenyatta adding that relevant authorities will establish the cause fire.
 Nairobi Governor Mike Sonko reiterated he will conduct an inspection of other private and public schools to ensure dormitories have enough fire exits. 
